Sentencas: The electrochemical characteristics of Ni|YSZ|LSM and Ni-Cu|YSZ|LSM single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells fed with a methane-air mixture ([CH4]/[O-2] molar ratio of 2) in a temperature range of 550-700 degrees C have been studied.
Titulo: Performance of Single-Chamber Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Ni and Ni-Cu Alloy Anodes and Fed with a Methane-Air Mixture

Sentencas: It has been shown that these devices generate electrical power.
Titulo: Performance of Single-Chamber Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Ni and Ni-Cu Alloy Anodes and Fed with a Methane-Air Mixture

Sentencas: The addition of copper to nickel improves the electrochemical characteristics; this fact is apparently attributed to the higher electronic conductivity of the anode material.
Titulo: Performance of Single-Chamber Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Ni and Ni-Cu Alloy Anodes and Fed with a Methane-Air Mixture

Sentencas: The maximum specific power value is 17 mW/cm(2) at a temperature of 700 degrees C and a flow rate of the methane-air mixture of 240 cm(3)/min.
Titulo: Performance of Single-Chamber Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Ni and Ni-Cu Alloy Anodes and Fed with a Methane-Air Mixture
